page.title: 13HEDGEROW,WEDMORE MOOR
page.content: WE WENT ON A HEDGEROW STUDY IN EARLY JULY.THE HEDGEROW WAS SITUATED AT THE EDGE OF THE BLOCK ON THE EDGE OF THE MOORLAND. WE STUDIED A 30 METRE STRETCH OF THE WILD HEDGEROW LOOKING AT ONE SIDE OF IT.2 THIRDS OF THE HEDGE CONSISTED OF BLACKTHORN,1 THIRD OF HAWTHORN, THESE WERE SO DENSE THAT IT WAS DIFFICULT TO COUNT THE NUMBERS. OTHER PLANTS FOUND IN THE HEDGE WERE DOGROSE 4 BLACKBERRY 20 BUTTERCUP 50 RED CAMPION 3 FROG-BIT 27 LUCERNE 2 SELF-HEAL 2 IVY 2 THISTLE 50 DOCK 18 COW PARSLEY 21
